    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1230"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1230">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/1574</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 7 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4244. Department’s telegram 3036, March 14.<note n="1" xml:id="d1230fn1">See <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_926">p. 926</ref>, footnote
                        1.</note> Foreign Office informs me that French Government does not see its
                    way to permit the landing of supplies for Jewish hospitals at Jerusalem owing to
                    their objection to any modification of blockade of Syrian coast. British
                    Government shares the view expressed by French Government and to its great
                    regret is accordingly unable to agree to this humanitarian proposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
